sentences: Red Tide began as a thrash metal outfit in 1993 then evolved into a jazz metal band in the late 1990s.
Red Tide began as a thrash metal outfit in 1993 then evolved into a jazz metal band in the late 1990s.
Red Tide disbanded in 2002 as there was a general lack of interest in continuing (cited by interview).
Foley joined Killswitch Engage after the departure of the previous drummer, Tom Gomes, in October 2003.
Foley also plays drums on metalcore band Unearth's 2011 album, Darkness in the Light filling in for departed drummer Derek Kerswill.

Unearth - Darkness in the Light (July 4, 2011; Metal Blade Records)
